<!DOCTYPE html>
<html data-ng-app="spaceFrontierApp">
<% include header %>


<body data-ng-controller="homeController">  
    <% include navbar %>  

    <section class="module parallax parallax-large parallax-1">
        <div class="container" id="parallax">
            <h1>SPACE Tool</h1>
            <h3>Science Payloads and Advanced Concepts for Exploration Interactive</h3>
            <p>Provides a basic system for a deep space CubeSat based off of user specifications for a mission.</p>
            <a style="margin-left:470px; color:white" id="rcorners" type="button" id="roundedbutton" href="\tool" class="btn btn-lg" style="color: #FFFFFF">Try it Now</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module content">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 style="text-align:center; font-size:60px">What Are CubeSats?</h1>
            <hr>
            <p>CubeSats, or as we like to call them "cute sats", are small satelites coming in 10 cm x 10 cm x 10 cm units weighing about 1.33 kg. A satelite can consist of up to 12 units; no bigger than a shoebox! CubeSats are grouped under the umbrella category of nanosatellites as their total masses are under 500 kg.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module parallax parallax-small parallax-2">
    <div class="container" id="parallax">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-2">
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-10">
                <p><br><br></p>
                <p style="text-align:right; font-size:30px; background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);">
                In 1999, the CubeSat was first introduced when Bob Twigs and Jordi Purig-Surai introduced a satellite blueprint to allow graduate students to develop and test small, low cost spacecraft in low earth orbit. Since then the idea of a low cost space exploration method has become increasingly popular propagating CubeSat development in the professional market.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module content">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 style="text-align:center; font-size:60px">Why CubeSats?</h1>
            <hr>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="group">
                    <div class="col-lg-3" style="margin-left:-100px">
                        <div class="card effect__hover">
                            <div class="card__front">
                                <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:50px;">Entry to Deep Space</p></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card__back">
                                <span class="card__text"><br>CubeSats already <br>exist in earth orbit, but the next <br>stage of development involves sending them to the further reaches of our solar system for lower costs.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3">
                        <div class="card effect__hover">
                            <div class="card__front">
                                <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:65px;">Form Factor</p></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card__back">
                                <span class="card__text"><br>The shape and size of <br>CubeSats allow them to be more compact and sturdy than larger <br>satellites which require more structural planning.</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3">
                        <div class="card effect__hover">
                            <div class="card__front">
                                <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:50px;">Standardized Platform</p></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card__back">
                                <span class="card__text"><br>CubeSat standardization <br>several planned and tested <br>methods of deploying missions from swarms to individual satellites ranging in size. </span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-3">
                        <div class="card effect__hover">
                            <div class="card__front">
                                <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:50px;">More Scientific Returns</p></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="card__back">
                                <span class="card__text"><br>By sending several CubeSats <br>with many different instruments out, <br>CubeSats offer more scientific returns from the variety of data that can be collected from one small, cheap mission. </span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="dividerlargest"></div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-3" style="margin-left:-100px">
                    <div class="card effect__hover">
                        <div class="card__front">
                            <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:60px;">Predictability<p></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card__back">
                            <span class="card__text"><br>The standardization of <br>CubeSats reduces the risks <br>associated with launches which are more frequent fears for large scale satellites.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-3">
                    <div class="card effect__hover">
                        <div class="card__front">
                            <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:44px;">Reduced Launch Costs</p></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card__back">
                            <span class="card__text">Launch costs <br>for space equipment <br> are calculated by mass units. <br>For example, it currently costs $10k/pound going into earth orbit. The low mass of CubeSats from their<br> size cuts launch costs.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-3">
                    <div class="card effect__hover">
                        <div class="card__front">
                            <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:40px;">Multiple <br>Platform Missions</p></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card__back">
                            <span class="card__text">CubeSats <br>can be sent out in <br>swarms, to research one objective togethor. Losing one or two cheap CubeSats, won't have as big as an impact of losing functionality <br>a large satellite.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-3">
                    <div class="card effect__hover">
                        <div class="card__front">
                            <span class="card__text"><p style="font-size:24px;margin-top:50px;">Disruptive Science!</p></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card__back">
                            <span class="card__text"><br>The low cost of CubeSats <br>relative to their traditional <br>counterparts disrupts the old market <br>of large scale satellite development for <br>deep space exploration.</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="dividerbiggest"></div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module parallax parallax-small parallax-3">
    <div class="container" id="parallax">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4">
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-8">
                <p style="text-align:right; font-size:30px"><br><br><br><br><br><br>To date, there have been over 300 CubeSat missions identified, and the list continues to grow!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module content">
        <div class="container">
            <h3 style="text-align:center; font-size:50px">Challenges Facing Deep Space Cubesats</h3>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:120px">Short Lifespan</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>CubeSats currently have an average lifespan of about a year in Low Earth orbit. But as deep space developments take place, lifespans can increase with better propulsion systems.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:70px">Form Factor Limits Available Space for Fuel/Propulsion Units</p></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text">The standardized volume of CubeSats, in multiple 10 cm x 10 cm x 10 cm units decreases the room available for propulsion units key to extending CubeSat lifespan. CubeSats however are currently standardized up to 27 U.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div style="background-image:url(/img/2.jpg); background-size:cover" class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br><br>An artist's depiction of a swarm of 3 single unit (1U) CubeSats orbitting the earth.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:100px">Higher Radiation</br>Levels</p></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text">Deep Space CubeSats are exposed to more radiation as they no longer fall under the protection of earth's magnetic field. Radiation can damage electronics. CubeSats now carry radiation protection, potentially by generating their own magnetic fields.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="dividertinier"></div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div style="background-image:url(/img/1.jpg); background-size:cover" class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard_text"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>An artist's depiction of a single multiunit CubeSat with deployable antennas orbitting the earth.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover" id="2">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:70px">Communication Range is Much Greater</p></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br>As CubeSats move further away from the earth, they must use stronger signals and more expensive antennas and radios to broadcast information back home.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><p style="font-size:30px; margin-top:70px">Difficulty Generating Power When Away from the Sun</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text">Deep Space recieves less sunlight to power solar panels. CubeSats due to their size generally have smaller solar panels and generate less power. However, CubeSat panels have the option to be deployable for a greater surface area to capture sunlight.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rcard effect__hover">
                    <div style="background-image:url(/img/3.jpg); background-size:cover" class="rcard__front">
                        <span class="rcard__text"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rcard__back">
                        <span class="rcard__text"><br><br>An artist's illustration of a multi unit 2 CubeSat swarm with deployable panels oribting the moon.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module parallax parallax-small parallax-4">
    <div class="container" id="parallax">
        <h1><a href="/tool" style="color:white">Create your CubeSat today!</a></h1>
    </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="container">
        <% include footer %>
    </div>
    <div class = "divider"></div>
</body>
</html>

         